HEADWORD: Subjected
<hw>Sub*ject"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Subjacent.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Led them direct . . . to the
<xex>subjected</xex> plain.⟦rdquo⟧ <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Reduced to subjection; brought under the dominion of
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Exposed; liable; subject; obnoxious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subjection</ent>⟦br⟧
